Embed-Preset HTTP 500 — Root Cause Trace
Date: 2026-05-23

== Server-side exception (from route.ts catch block) ==

Error: No collection.anki2 found in .apkg
    at POST (app/api/embed-preset/route.ts:169)
    caught at line 240: console.error("[embed-preset] Processing error:", err)
    returned as: NextResponse.json({ error: "Export failed. Please try again." }, { status: 500 })

== Root cause ==

Commit e16e204 ("revert anki21b: use collection.anki2 exclusively; drop anki21b fallback")
changed app/api/embed-preset/route.ts to look ONLY for "collection.anki2":

    const dbFilename = "collection.anki2";
    const dbFile = zip.file(dbFilename);
    if (!dbFile) throw new Error("No collection.anki2 found in .apkg");

But scripts/test-embed-preset.ts createSyntheticApkg() was never updated and still packs
the SQLite database as "collection.anki21b" (line 166):

    zip.file("collection.anki21b", dbBytes);   // <-- stale; route can't find this

This mismatch means every test POST sends an .apkg the route cannot read → 500.

== Secondary issue (would cause assertion failures after 500 is fixed) ==

Commit 668bb68 ("fix embed-preset: store steps in minutes, not seconds") renamed
parseStepsToSeconds → parseStepsToMinutes in the route and changed the conversion math.

The test script's parseStepsToSeconds helper (line 131–140) was NOT updated — it still
converts to seconds (× 60 for "m" suffix). The assertions on lines 248–249 would therefore
compare route-written minutes against test-expected seconds and fail for every case.

== Fix applied ==

1. scripts/test-embed-preset.ts line 166: "collection.anki21b" → "collection.anki2"
2. scripts/test-embed-preset.ts parseStepsToSeconds renamed to parseStepsToMinutes
   with matching conversion math (identical to route's parseStepsToMinutes)
3. Lines 248–249: parseStepsToSeconds(...) → parseStepsToMinutes(...)
4. Comment on line 131 updated to reflect minutes storage

== Commits responsible ==

e16e204  revert anki21b: use collection.anki2 exclusively; drop anki21b fallback
668bb68  fix embed-preset: store steps in minutes, not seconds (collection.anki2 format)

Both commits correctly updated the route but did not update the test script.
